results.occurrenceRemarks: COMMON NAMES: Little hogweed, moss rose, pigweed, purslane, pursley, pussley, verdolaga. DESCRIPTION: Purslane has succulent oval leaves and smooth reddish stems. Its small yellow flowers have five petals. FLAVOR This highly coveted plant has a slightly salty, lemony taste. HABITAT This hardy plant is common throughout North America. Purslane thrives in rich soil with full sun, but it can be found along roadsides and trail sides, springing up from sidewalk cracks, and in waste areas. SEASON Purslane grows from early spring to late fall. EDIBLE PARTS Flowers, leaves, seeds, stems, and tips.
